# E:\MURALI\NEST-JS\testapp>

**NestJS CLI commands** to generate everything needed for the controller + custom pipe setup.

---

# 🚀 1. Generate Users Module

```bash
nest g module users
```

---

# 🚀 2. Generate Users Controller

```bash
nest g controller users
```

---

# 🚀 3. (Optional but Recommended) Generate Service

Even if not used now, good practice:

```bash
nest g service users
```

---

# 🚀 4. Generate Custom Pipe

```bash
nest g pipe users/pipes/trim
```

👉 This will create:

```
src/users/pipes/trim.pipe.ts
```

---

# 📁 Final Folder Structure

After running above commands:

```
src/
 ├── app.module.ts
 ├── users/
 │    ├── users.module.ts
 │    ├── users.controller.ts
 │    ├── users.service.ts
 │    └── pipes/
 │         └── trim.pipe.ts
```

---

# 🔧 5. Install Required Packages (IMPORTANT)

For ValidationPipe + Transform:

```bash
npm install class-validator class-transformer
```

---

# 🔧 6. Enable Global ValidationPipe

Update `main.ts`:

```ts
import { ValidationPipe } from '@nestjs/common';

app.useGlobalPipes(
  new ValidationPipe({
    whitelist: true,
    transform: true,
    forbidNonWhitelisted: true,
  }),
);
```

---

# 🔧 7. Import UsersModule into AppModule

```ts
import { UsersModule } from './users/users.module';

@Module({
  imports: [UsersModule],
})
export class AppModule {}
```

---

# 🔥 That’s it!

Now paste:

- ✅ `users.controller.ts` → inside `users` folder
- ✅ `trim.pipe.ts` → inside `users/pipes`

Run:

```bash
npm run start:dev
```
